<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1955,2017]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1955,1981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2003" box="[276,609,1955,1981]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picticornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[276,365,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[383,472,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Bisaltes</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[489,609,1955,1980]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">picticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on 
<specimenCount box="[895,1011,1955,1981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1083,1165,1955,1981]" name="Bolivia" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1182,1236,1955,1981]" country="Bolivia" name="Beni" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Beni</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1295,1424,1955,1981]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Audureau, A." box="[151,346,1991,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" pagination="60 - 68" refId="ref4173" refString="Audureau, A. (2016) Notes sur les Apomecynini du Perou (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Les Cahiers Magellanes, 23, 60 - 68." type="journal article" year="2016">Audureau (2016)</bibRefCitation>
expanded the geographical distribution to 
<collectingCountry box="[837,892,1991,2017]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="96">Peru</collectingCountry>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[1061,1354,1991,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="96" pagination="379 - 383" refId="ref4891" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (2003) Notas e descricoes em Bisaltes Thomson, 1868 e Ptericoptus Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1830 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Apomecynini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 47 (3), 379 - 383. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262003000300003" type="journal article" year="2003">Galileo &amp; Martins (2003)</bibRefCitation>
(translated): “The color pattern of 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark, 2022" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[471,736,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picticornis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[471,560,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[575,600,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[616,736,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">picticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[742,829,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
reminds us of the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1830" box="[1152,1281,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Ptericoptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1152,1281,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Ptericoptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is unique in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[180,269,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[180,269,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Bisaltes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with the center of the pronotum widely occupied by a black band. The only species that have this band are 
<taxonomicName authority="Tippmann, 1960" authorityName="Tippmann" authorityYear="1960" box="[194,532,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis box="[194,338,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B. monticola</emphasis>
Tippmann, 1960
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Burmeister, 1865)" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[589,929,222,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adustus">
<emphasis box="[589,707,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B. adustus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Burmeister, H. C." box="[723,920,222,249]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" pagination="156 - 181" refId="ref4861" refString="Burmeister, H. C. (1865) Longicornia Argentina. Systematische Uebersicht der Bockkafer der La Plata-Staaten. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 26, 156 - 181." type="journal article" year="1865">Burmeister, 1865</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
but the body pubescence, in both species, is yellowish orange, the antennae have black integument, and the apical half of the elytra is entirely black.” However, the elytral and pronotal pubescent pattern in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bruch, 1911" authorityName="Bruch" authorityYear="1911" box="[643,1118,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spegazzinii" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[643,732,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[747,836,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Bisaltes</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[851,975,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">spegazzinii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bruch, C." box="[981,1118,295,321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" pagination="164 - 178" refId="ref4782" refString="Bruch, C. (1911) Longicornios argentinos nuevos o poco conocidos. II. Revista del Museo de La Plata, 18, 164 - 178." type="journal article" year="1911">Bruch, 1911</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is highly variable: the longitudinal yellowish-brown pubescent band on the center of the pronotum can be from very narrow (as in the 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[181,382,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picticornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[181,206,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[222,246,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[262,382,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">picticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[389,403,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">–</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[410,476,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–14. 7–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[192,1396,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[192,1396,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–14. 7–10) Bisaltes (Bisaltes) picticornis Galileo &amp; Martins, 2003, holotype male: 7) Dorsal habitus; 8) Ventral habitus; 9) Lateral habitus; 10) Labels. 11–14) Bisaltes (Bisaltes) taua Galileo &amp; Martins, 2003, holotype female: 11a-c) Labels; 12) Dorsal habitus; 13) Ventral habitus; 14) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825629/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) to very wide, making the black longitudinal bands very narrow, with several degrees linking these two extremes; the scutellum can be entirely black, entirely covered by yellowish-brown pubescence, or have a longitudinal yellowish-brown pubescent band; and the black central band on the anterior region of the elytra is variable in length and width, reaching from the apex of the anterior third to slightly beyond the middle. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bruch" authorityYear="1911" box="[222,427,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spegazzinii" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[222,247,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[263,287,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[303,427,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">spegazzinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has already been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[792,874,511,537]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(now, including 
<collectingCountry box="[1064,1120,511,537]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Peru</collectingCountry>
). Therefore, we synonymize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Bezark" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,352,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picticornis" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[151,176,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[192,216,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[232,352,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">picticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bruch" authorityYear="1911" box="[416,620,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spegazzinii" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[416,440,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[456,480,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">B.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[496,620,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">spegazzinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[636,721,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26. 22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[152,1433,181,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[151,1436,181,1672]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. 22) Bisaltes strandi Breuning, 1940, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 23) Bisaltes fuscoapicalis Breuning, 1950, holotype female, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 24) Bisaltes subreticulatus Aurivillius, 1920, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure. 25) Bisaltes spegazzinii Bruch, 1911, syntype, from the original description. 26) Bisaltes venezuelensis Breuning, 1943, holotype, by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825635/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
